            <!---========= Start Benefits Of Learning Management Systems===============-->
            <section class="my-5" id="Benefits">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6 text-center p-5">
                            <img loading="lazy" src="img/Benefits-of-LMS.webp" class="img-fluid" alt="LMS-banner" width="356" height="442">
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mt-md-5 mt-sm-0">
                            <img loading="lazy" src="img/Benefits-of-LMS-icons.webp" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="LMS-banner" width="81" height="81">
                            <h2 class="h2__heading2 animate__fadeInDown wow animated"><span>Benefits Of</span><br />
                                Learning Management Systems</h2>
                            <p><i class="fa-solid fa-caret-right "></i><strong>Quick Feedback : </strong>LMS let's instructors provide immediate feedback to students, thereby bridging the learning gap and improving their academic performance.</p>
                            <p><i class="fa-solid fa-caret-right "></i><strong>Cost-Effective : </strong>It eliminates the need for a physical classroom. It reduces the cost of printing & distribution of learning materials, thereby enabling schools to allocate resources efficiently.</p>
                            <p><i class="fa-solid fa-caret-right "></i><strong>Better Learning Outcomes : </strong>LMS offers personalized learning paths tailored to each learner’s needs along with the ability to learn at their own pace, thereby boosting learning outcomes.</p>
                            <p><i class="fa-solid fa-caret-right "></i><strong>Highly Scalable : </strong>LMS can accommodate a large number of students making it ideal for institutions with increasing student enrolments.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!---========= End Benefits Of Learning Management Systems===============-->

            <!---=========Start Types of Learning Management System ===============-->
            <section class="my-5 lms-type">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <img loading="lazy" src="img/Types-of-LMS-Icons.webp" class="img-fluid" alt="LMS-banner" width="81" height="81">
                            <h2 class="h2__heading2 mt-3"><span>Types Of</span>
                                <br />
                                Learning Management Systems</h2>
                            <div class="p-3 border rounded mt-5 ">
                                <h4 class="fw-bold text-orange">1. Integrated LMS</h4>
                                <p>Learning Management Systems can be integrated with scheduling, internal calendars, and mailing service; also with other ERP systems such as SIS, attendance management, payroll management, fee management, etc. This Learning Management Systems offers a unified view of all the users across the institution.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-md-6 text-center mt-md-5 mt-sm-0">
                            <img loading="lazy" src="img/Types-of-LMS.webp" class="img-fluid mt-5" alt="LMS-banner" width="488" height="411">
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mt-3">
                            <div class="h-100 p-3 border rounded">
                                <h4 class="fw-bold text-orange">2. Open-Source LMS vs Closed Source LMS</h4>
                                <p>Open Source Learning Management Systems offers complete freedom and flexibility with customization options. It helps to schedule and design priority features rather than waiting to be provided by the ERP vendor. Whereas, closed source Learning Management Systems is a proprietary code. The customization is carried out by the LMS owner and can be made available as a SaaS application on the cloud.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mt-3">
                            <div class="h-100 p-3 border rounded">
                                <h4 class="fw-bold text-orange">3. Free LMS vs Commercial LMS</h4>
                                <p>Free Learning Management Systems is free to use & can be downloaded easily & installed on the institution’s servers. It only has basic features such as course management, content creation, etc. Whereas, commercial Learning Management Systems requires a license fee, & the cost varies depending on  features & the number of users. It has advanced capabilities of analytics, BI reporting tools, gamification, etc.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mt-3">
                            <div class="h-100 p-3 border rounded">
                                <h4 class="fw-bold text-orange">4. SaaS LMS/Cloud-Based LMS vs Hosted LMS</h4>
                                <p>Saas Learning Management Systems is hosted on the ERP provider’s servers and is accessible via the internet. It is offered on a subscription basis where the school pays a monthly/yearly fee. However, hosted LMS is installed on the institution’s servers and managed by their IT department. It requires an upfront capital investment in software, hardware, and other IT services.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 mt-3">
                            <div class="h-100 p-3 border rounded">
                                <h4 class="fw-bold text-orange">5. Corporate LMS vs Academic LMS</h4>
                                <p>Corporate LMS is developed for employee training & development in the corporate sector. It mainly focuses on job-related skills, professional development, and compliance training. Whereas, academic LMS is specifically designed for education and training in universities, schools, and colleges. It focuses on curriculum content and academic courses.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <!---========= End Types of Learning Management System===============-->

